content:
Nothing, also known as an empty roll, is a possible drop that can be found on many monsters in Old School RuneScape. This is associated mainly with low-level to medium-level monster drop tables and the rare drop table/gem drop table. Equipping a ring of wealth will remove all empty rolls from the rare drop table and gem drop table, increasing the likelihood of obtaining a more valuable drop.

In the case where a monster rolls their drop table more than once, for example the Alchemical Hydra, the empty roll affects only one roll at a time.
rawContent:
[[File:Bank filler.png|left]] '''Nothing''', also known as an empty roll, is a possible drop that can be found on many monsters in [[Old School RuneScape]]. This is associated mainly with low-level to medium-level monster drop tables and the [[rare drop table]]/[[gem drop table]]. Equipping a [[ring of wealth]] will remove all empty rolls from the rare drop table and gem drop table, increasing the likelihood of obtaining a more valuable drop.

In the case where a monster rolls their drop table more than once, for example the [[Alchemical Hydra]], the empty roll affects only one roll at a time.

[[Category:Mechanics]]
